Description: GPU-accelerated signal processing framework
 CyberEther is a high-performance GPU-accelerated framework for real-time
 signal visualization and data processing. It leverages low-level graphics
 APIs (Vulkan, Metal, WebGPU) to achieve native performance on any platform.
 .
 Features include a modern flowgraph editor, low-latency remote interface,
 and Python API for custom signal visualization via Superluminal.
